A 30-year-old man, Chukwuebuka Udeh has blamed alcoholic drink after he defiled a 5-year-old girl.
DAILY POST reports that the suspect was among 12 others paraded by the Enugu State Commissioner of Police, Mohammed Ndatsu Aliyu. The act was said to have been committed at Obinagu Community, Udi L.G.A. of the State.
Ude, who confessed to the offence, said he was drunk when the incident happened. He said, “I was drunk on that faithful day when some children came to my house to play, so one of them entered my room and I played with her body and laps.” More to come…